attributes.name: Right lung
phrases:
FINDINGS:  Since prior exam, there is a new right-sided pleural effusion with
 some associated right basilar consolidation, which is likely atelectasis.

The apices of the lungs are
 clear.
There is no pulmonary edema or pneumothorax.

IMPRESSION:
 1.  New small-to-moderate sized right pleural effusion.
2.  Bibasilar opacities, likely atelectasis.

In the proper clinical setting,
 infection cannot be completely excluded.
